[2] PAHO: complications and sequelae of COVID-19
Date: Wed 12 Aug 2020
Source: WHO/PAHO [abridged, edited]
https://www.paho.org/en/documents/epidemiological-alert-complications-and-sequelae-covid-19-12-august-2020


More than 7 months following the 1st report of novel coronavirus disease (COVID-19), knowledge of the complications and sequelae of this disease has increased substantially. Through this alert, the Pan American Health Organization/World Health Organization (PAHO/WHO) urges Member States to keep health professionals informed as new information continues to become available in order to strengthen the timely detection and proper management of COVID-19 cases, complications, and sequelae.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is a comprehensive document with different sections: complications from COVID-19; sequelae due to COVID-19 including respiratory, cardiovascular, neuropsychiatric, and psychological changes; guidance for national authorities on acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS); septic shock; prevention of complications in hospitalized patients and critically ill patients with COVID-19; management of neurological and mental manifestations associated with COVID-19. - Mod.UBA]

